# Kit-Managed Directories (READ-ONLY)

The following directories are **junctions to the shared GAB Agents Kit** (`~/.gab-agents/`). They are version-controlled, auto-synced across all team members, and must NOT be modified from a workspace context.

## Protected Directories

| Directory | Junction Target | Contains |
|-----------|----------------|----------|
| `agents/` | `~/.gab-agents/agents/` | Agent documentation (AGENTS.GAB.md, schema/*.md, gab/*.md) |
| `skills/` | `~/.gab-agents/skills/` | Skill definitions (gab-lint, gab-sign, gab-run, gab-test-debug, etc.) |
| `.cursor/rules/` | `~/.gab-agents/cursor-rules/` | Cursor rule files (*.mdc) |
| `.cursor/hooks/` | `~/.gab-agents/cursor-hooks/` | Cursor hook scripts |

## Rules

1. **NEVER create new files** in these directories. New files would be pushed to all team members on next sync.
2. **NEVER modify existing files** in these directories from a workspace. Changes belong in the kit repo (`~/.gab-agents/`) and must go through the version bump + push workflow.
3. **NEVER delete files** in these directories. Deletions propagate to all users.

## Where to Put Project-Specific Content

| Content Type | Correct Location |
|--------------|-----------------|
| Project notes, architecture, memories | `AGENTS.PROJECT.md` (workspace root) |
| Project-specific Cursor rules | Create in workspace root as standalone `.mdc` (NOT in `.cursor/rules/`) |
| Test scripts, demos | `test/` directory |
| Source code (DLLs, extensions) | `src/` directory |
| Documentation | `docs/` directory |

## If You Need to Change the Kit

Tell the user: "This change affects the shared agent kit. Should I make this change in `~/.gab-agents/` and push it to the team?" Then:
1. Edit the file in `~/.gab-agents/` directly (NOT through the junction)
2. Run `bump-version.ps1`
3. Commit and push

The junction will reflect the change immediately in all workspaces.
